title: Drawing, "Cabinet", ca. 1929–30
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Small stamp in red ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite in lower right corner: #/7113 [circled]; dimensions in graphite; lower right corner in red color pencil: P
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing of cabinet, probably meant to be placed in a corner. Three squared edges, rounded edge at front. Open shelf on two sides, cabinet below and smaller base at floor. Cabinet in wood, top of unit and base in darker material. Long vertical, rectangular pull on cabinet door.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Cabinet", ca. 1929–30.
ca. 1929–30. Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite. Gift of Donald Deskey. 1988-101-1263.
